 06169114 Photo; PHOTO: AP File Photograph; STORM WATCH -- It's been 27 years since a hurricane hit Miami, making some experts nervous about an overdue big storm.
 The great storms have made fictional plots of B movies and unmade real dreams of people who would implant civilization in an environment that could be swallowed up by nature in a moment.; A hurricane ended the dream of a railroad down the Florida Keys in 1935 and virtually isolated Key West for two years.
